{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DuTTB9sLTwMcYLR6Sm4gT7","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Plan: Add Compodoc to Storybook\n2\t\n3\t## Strategic Direction\n4\t\n5\tFrom the advisor (steps 1-3 and 5 are correct; step 4 is corrected below based on\n6\tverified Storybook 10.3.5 internals -- `@compodoc/documentation` does not exist as\n7\tan npm package; the actual mechanism is `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` set in\n8\t`preview.ts`):\n9\t\n10\t1. Add `@compodoc/compodoc` `^1.1.26` to root `package.json` devDependencies and run\n11\t   `npm install` to pin it explicitly rather than relying on the transitive resolution.\n12\t2. Flip `\"compodoc\": false` to `\"compodoc\": true` on both `storybook` and\n13\t   `build-storybook` targets in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`; leave\n14\t   `compodocArgs` unset to accept the `[\"-e\", \"json\"]` default.\n15\t3. Create `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` extending\n16\t   `./tsconfig.json` with `\"include\": [\"../src/**/*.ts\"]` and\n17\t   `\"exclude\": [\"../**/*.spec.ts\", \"../**/*.stories.ts\"]` so compodoc analyzes only\n18\t   library sources.\n19\t4. [Corrected] Update `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts` to\n20\t   import `documentation.json` from the workspace root and assign it to\n21\t   `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` -- the mechanism `@storybook/angular` 10.3.5\n22\t   uses internally to wire compodoc data into `extractArgTypes` and\n23\t   `extractComponentDescription`. The `setCompodocJson` API no longer exists in this\n24\t   version. The `@compodoc/documentation` addon referenced in the advisor's step 4\n25\t   does not exist as an npm package.\n26\t5. Run `npm exec nx storybook ngx-smart-components` and confirm `documentation.json`\n27\t   is generated at the workspace root and the Docs tab shows component metadata.\n28\t\n29\t## Steps\n30\t\n31\t1. **Pin `@compodoc/compodoc` as a direct devDependency**\n32\t   - File: `package.json`\n33\t   - Change: Add `\"@compodoc/compodoc\": \"^1.2.1\"` to `devDependencies`. Use `^1.2.1`\n34\t     to match the currently-installed transitive version (1.2.1) and avoid an\n35\t     unnecessary downgrade.\n36\t   - Rationale: Currently only a transitive dep; pinning prevents unintended version\n37\t     drift if the parent package changes its dependency range.\n38\t\n39\t2. **Enable compodoc in the Storybook Nx targets**\n40\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n41\t   - Change: Set `\"compodoc\": true` in the `options` block of both `storybook` and\n42\t     `build-storybook` targets (currently `false` in both). Leave `compodocArgs`\n43\t     unset; the builder's default `[\"-e\", \"json\"]` is correct.\n44\t   - Rationale: The `@storybook/angular` executor runs compodoc automatically before\n45\t     Storybook when `compodoc: true`. It adds `-p <tsconfig> -d <workspace root>`\n46\t     automatically, writing `documentation.json` to the workspace root.\n47\t\n48\t3. **Create `tsconfig.doc.json` for compodoc**\n49\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json`\n50\t   - Change: Create with the following content:\n51\t     ```json\n52\t     {\n53\t       \"extends\": \"./tsconfig.json\",\n54\t       \"include\": [\"../src/**/*.ts\"],\n55\t       \"exclude\": [\"../**/*.spec.ts\", \"../**/*.stories.ts\"]\n56\t     }\n57\t     ```\n58\t   - Rationale: The builder searches for `tsconfig.doc.json` starting from the\n59\t     `.storybook/` configDir. Without it, compodoc analyzes the project's default\n60\t     tsconfig which includes test and story files. This file scopes compodoc to\n61\t     library source files only.\n62\t\n63\t4. **Wire `documentation.json` into the Storybook preview**\n64\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`\n65\t   - Change: Replace the empty file with:\n66\t     ```typescript\n67\t     import { global } from '@storybook/global';\n68\t     import docJson from '../../../documentation.json';\n69\t\n70\t     global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;\n71\t     ```\n72\t   - Rationale: `@storybook/angular` 10.3.5 reads `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__`\n73\t     in its `extractArgTypes` and `extractComponentDescription` functions (wired into\n74\t     `parameters.docs`). The builder's `-d <workspace root>` places `documentation.json`\n75\t     at the workspace root, three levels above the `.storybook/` directory.\n76\t     `@storybook/global` is already installed as a dependency of Storybook.\n77\t\n78\t5. **Add `resolveJsonModule` to the Storybook tsconfig**\n79\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json`\n80\t   - Change: Add `\"resolveJsonModule\": true` to `compilerOptions` so TypeScript can\n81\t     import `documentation.json` in `preview.ts`.\n82\t   - Rationale: Without this flag, `import docJson from '../../../documentation.json'`\n83\t     will fail with a TypeScript compile error.\n84\t\n85\t6. **Verify the integration**\n86\t   - Command: `npm exec nx storybook ngx-smart-components`\n87\t   - Verify: `documentation.json` appears at the workspace root after the builder runs.\n88\t   - Verify: The Docs tab for `NgxSmartComponents` shows input/output metadata.\n89\t   - If `documentation.json` is missing or the Docs tab is empty, add\n90\t     `\"compodocArgs\": [\"-e\", \"json\"]` explicitly to the target options and rerun.\n91\t\n92\t## Key Decisions\n93\t\n94\t- **Use builder-native `compodoc: true` rather than a npm `scripts` approach**: The\n95\t  `@storybook/angular` executor handles running compodoc and passing the right `-p` and\n96\t  `-d` flags automatically. A `package.json` script would duplicate this logic and\n97\t  require manual coordination with nx targets.\n98\t- **`global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` instead of `setCompodocJson`**: The\n99\t  `setCompodocJson` API was removed in Storybook 10.x. The source code confirms the\n100\t  global variable is still the bridge; assigning to it directly in `preview.ts` is the\n101\t  correct replacement.\n102\t- **`tsconfig.doc.json` scoped to library sources**: Including spec and story files in\n103\t  compodoc analysis produces noise (test helpers, mock components) in the Docs tab.\n104\t  Excluding them keeps documentation clean.\n105\t- **Risk -- `documentation.json` path**: The builder always writes to workspace root via\n106\t  `-d <workspace root>`. If the path assumption (`../../../documentation.json` from\n107\t  `.storybook/`) proves wrong, check the actual output path after first run and adjust\n108\t  the import accordingly.\n109\t\n110\t## Dependencies\n111\t\n112\tSteps 1-3 are independent and can be done in parallel. Step 4 depends on step 3\n113\t(tsconfig.doc.json must exist for the import resolution to work correctly at build\n114\ttime). Step 5 depends on step 4 (resolveJsonModule must be set before preview.ts\n115\tcompiles). Step 6 (verification) depends on all prior steps.\n116\t\n117\tSequential order: [1, 2, 3] in parallel, then 4, then 5, then 6.\n118\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40596bc0-ad7c-4072-a632-7fd07f4bf8b4","uuid":"699f7f05-3046-4cff-81b5-bf2e51fc1c0a","timestamp":"2026-04-24T08:18:24.228Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"D:\\projects\\github\\LayZeeDK\\ngx-smart-components\\plans\\add-compodoc-to-storybook.plan.md","content":"# Plan: Add Compodoc to Storybook\n\n## Strategic Direction\n\nFrom the advisor (steps 1-3 and 5 are correct; step 4 is corrected below based on\nverified Storybook 10.3.5 internals -- `@compodoc/documentation` does not exist as\nan npm package; the actual mechanism is `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` set in\n`preview.ts`):\n\n1. Add `@compodoc/compodoc` `^1.1.26` to root `package.json` devDependencies and run\n   `npm install` to pin it explicitly rather than relying on the transitive resolution.\n2. Flip `\"compodoc\": false` to `\"compodoc\": true` on both `storybook` and\n   `build-storybook` targets in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`; leave\n   `compodocArgs` unset to accept the `[\"-e\", \"json\"]` default.\n3. Create `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` extending\n   `./tsconfig.json` with `\"include\": [\"../src/**/*.ts\"]` and\n   `\"exclude\": [\"../**/*.spec.ts\", \"../**/*.stories.ts\"]` so compodoc analyzes only\n   library sources.\n4. [Corrected] Update `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts` to\n   import `documentation.json` from the workspace root and assign it to\n   `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` -- the mechanism `@storybook/angular` 10.3.5\n   uses internally to wire compodoc data into `extractArgTypes` and\n   `extractComponentDescription`. The `setCompodocJson` API no longer exists in this\n   version. The `@compodoc/documentation` addon referenced in the advisor's step 4\n   does not exist as an npm package.\n5. Run `npm exec nx storybook ngx-smart-components` and confirm `documentation.json`\n   is generated at the workspace root and the Docs tab shows component metadata.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. **Pin `@compodoc/compodoc` as a direct devDependency**\n   - File: `package.json`\n   - Change: Add `\"@compodoc/compodoc\": \"^1.2.1\"` to `devDependencies`. Use `^1.2.1`\n     to match the currently-installed transitive version (1.2.1) and avoid an\n     unnecessary downgrade.\n   - Rationale: Currently only a transitive dep; pinning prevents unintended version\n     drift if the parent package changes its dependency range.\n\n2. **Enable compodoc in the Storybook Nx targets**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n   - Change: Set `\"compodoc\": true` in the `options` block of both `storybook` and\n     `build-storybook` targets (currently `false` in both). Leave `compodocArgs`\n     unset; the builder's default `[\"-e\", \"json\"]` is correct.\n   - Rationale: The `@storybook/angular` executor runs compodoc automatically before\n     Storybook when `compodoc: true`. It adds `-p <tsconfig> -d <workspace root>`\n     automatically, writing `documentation.json` to the workspace root.\n\n3. **Create `tsconfig.doc.json` for compodoc**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json`\n   - Change: Create with the following content:\n     ```json\n     {\n       \"extends\": \"./tsconfig.json\",\n       \"include\": [\"../src/**/*.ts\"],\n       \"exclude\": [\"../**/*.spec.ts\", \"../**/*.stories.ts\"]\n     }\n     ```\n   - Rationale: The builder searches for `tsconfig.doc.json` starting from the\n     `.storybook/` configDir. Without it, compodoc analyzes the project's default\n     tsconfig which includes test and story files. This file scopes compodoc to\n     library source files only.\n\n4. **Wire `documentation.json` into the Storybook preview**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`\n   - Change: Replace the empty file with:\n     ```typescript\n     import { global } from '@storybook/global';\n     import docJson from '../../../documentation.json';\n\n     global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;\n     ```\n   - Rationale: `@storybook/angular` 10.3.5 reads `global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__`\n     in its `extractArgTypes` and `extractComponentDescription` functions (wired into\n     `parameters.docs`). The builder's `-d <workspace root>` places `documentation.json`\n     at the workspace root, three levels above the `.storybook/` directory.\n     `@storybook/global` is already installed as a dependency of Storybook.\n\n5. **Add `resolveJsonModule` to the Storybook tsconfig**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json`\n   - Change: Add `\"resolveJsonModule\": true` to `compilerOptions` so TypeScript can\n     import `documentation.json` in `preview.ts`.\n   - Rationale: Without this flag, `import docJson from '../../../documentation.json'`\n     will fail with a TypeScript compile error.\n\n6. **Verify the integration**\n   - Command: `npm exec nx storybook ngx-smart-components`\n   - Verify: `documentation.json` appears at the workspace root after the builder runs.\n   - Verify: The Docs tab for `NgxSmartComponents` shows input/output metadata.\n   - If `documentation.json` is missing or the Docs tab is empty, add\n     `\"compodocArgs\": [\"-e\", \"json\"]` explicitly to the target options and rerun.\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n- **Use builder-native `compodoc: true` rather than a npm `scripts` approach**: The\n  `@storybook/angular` executor handles running compodoc and passing the right `-p` and\n  `-d` flags automatically. A `package.json` script would duplicate this logic and\n  require manual coordination with nx targets.\n- **`global.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__` instead of `setCompodocJson`**: The\n  `setCompodocJson` API was removed in Storybook 10.x. The source code confirms the\n  global variable is still the bridge; assigning to it directly in `preview.ts` is the\n  correct replacement.\n- **`tsconfig.doc.json` scoped to library sources**: Including spec and story files in\n  compodoc analysis produces noise (test helpers, mock components) in the Docs tab.\n  Excluding them keeps documentation clean.\n- **Risk -- `documentation.json` path**: The builder always writes to workspace root via\n  `-d <workspace root>`. If the path assumption (`../../../documentation.json` from\n  `.storybook/`) proves wrong, check the actual output path after first run and adjust\n  the import accordingly.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nSteps 1-3 are independent and can be done in parallel. Step 4 depends on step 3\n(tsconfig.doc.json must exist for the import resolution to work correctly at build\ntime). Step 5 depends on step 4 (resolveJsonModule must be set before preview.ts\ncompiles). Step 6 (verification) depends on all prior steps.\n\nSequential order: [1, 2, 3] in parallel, then 4, then 5, then 6.\n","numLines":118,"startLine":1,"totalLines":118}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019yb5wJXFWPu6a5TyAUBKQr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Plan: Fix Compodoc Task-Graph Lifecycle and Autodocs\n2\t\n3\t## Strategic Direction\n4\t\n5\t1. Add a separate `compodoc` target in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` using `nrwl/run-commands` (or `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`) with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` and `-e json -d {workspaceRoot}`.\n6\t2. Set `compodoc: false` on both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets and add `dependsOn: [\"compodoc\"]` -- this eliminates the double-run and makes the artifact contract visible to Nx.\n7\t3. Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the meta in `ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`; without it the compodoc JSON is dead weight.\n8\t4. Apply Finding 2: replace the cast with a `declare global` Window augmentation in `preview.ts`.\n9\t5. Run `npx nx reset && npx nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components` to validate cache inputs and autodocs rendering.\n10\t\n11\t## Steps\n12\t\n13\t1. **Add `compodoc` target to `project.json`**\n14\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n15\t   - Change: Add a new `compodoc` target using the `nx:run-commands` executor that invokes `@compodoc/compodoc` with `-p tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .` (workspace root). Set `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` so Nx can cache the artifact.\n16\t   - Example shape:\n17\t     ```json\n18\t     \"compodoc\": {\n19\t       \"executor\": \"nx:run-commands\",\n20\t       \"outputs\": [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"],\n21\t       \"options\": {\n22\t         \"command\": \"npx compodoc -p packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .\"\n23\t       }\n24\t     }\n25\t     ```\n26\t   - Rationale: Makes the compodoc artifact a first-class Nx output with cache tracking. Eliminates the silent coupling where `storybook`/`build-storybook` produce `documentation.json` as an invisible side-effect.\n27\t\n28\t2. **Disable executor-internal compodoc and wire `dependsOn`**\n29\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n30\t   - Change: In both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets, set `\"compodoc\": false` under `options` and add `\"dependsOn\": [\"compodoc\"]` at the target level (alongside `executor`, `outputs`, etc.).\n31\t   - Rationale: Prevents compodoc from running twice (once via `dependsOn`, once inside the executor). With `dependsOn`, Nx schedules `compodoc` before `storybook`/`build-storybook`, making the dependency visible in `nx graph` and CI logs.\n32\t\n33\t3. **Add `autodocs` tag to the story meta**\n34\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`\n35\t   - Change: Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the `meta` object:\n36\t     ```typescript\n37\t     const meta: Meta<NgxSmartComponents> = {\n38\t       component: NgxSmartComponents,\n39\t       title: 'NgxSmartComponents',\n40\t       tags: ['autodocs'],\n41\t     };\n42\t     ```\n43\t   - Rationale: Storybook 10 autodocs is tag-driven. Without this tag no autodocs page is generated, meaning the compodoc JSON loaded in `preview.ts` is never consumed. Adding the tag closes the loop: compodoc produces JSON -> preview loads it -> autodocs renders it.\n44\t\n45\t4. **Replace type cast with `declare global` Window augmentation (Finding 2 -- hygiene)**\n46\t   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`\n47\t   - Change: Remove the `(global as Record<string, unknown>)` cast and replace with a typed property access. Add a `declare global` block (can live in `documentation.d.ts` or directly in `preview.ts`):\n48\t     ```typescript\n49\t     declare global {\n50\t       interface Window {\n51\t         __STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__?: unknown;\n52\t       }\n53\t     }\n54\t     ```\n55\t     Then update the assignment to:\n56\t     ```typescript\n57\t     (global as Window)['__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__'] = docJson;\n58\t     ```\n59\t     Or, since `global` from `@storybook/global` resolves to `window` in the browser, simply:\n60\t     ```typescript\n61\t     window.__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;\n62\t     ```\n63\t   - Rationale: Restores type safety at zero runtime cost. The `declare global` block is the correct TypeScript idiom for extending `Window`.\n64\t\n65\t5. **Validate**\n66\t   - Command: `npx nx reset && npm exec nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components`\n67\t   - Expected: `compodoc` runs first (visible in task log), then `build-storybook` runs, `documentation.json` is produced at workspace root, autodocs page is generated for `NgxSmartComponents`.\n68\t   - Also run: `npm exec nx lint ngx-smart-components` to confirm no type errors in `.storybook/` after the cast removal.\n69\t\n70\t## Key Decisions\n71\t\n72\t- **Separate `compodoc` target vs. executor-internal**: The advisor confirmed that setting `compodoc: false` on the executor and introducing a `dependsOn` target eliminates the double-run risk. The internal compodoc flag is purely a convenience shortcut; removing it in favor of an explicit target is strictly better for Nx cache and observability.\n73\t- **`nx:run-commands` vs. `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`**: Either works. `nx:run-commands` avoids adding a new dependency; `@twittwer/compodoc` provides a typed executor schema. Use `nx:run-commands` unless the project already uses `@twittwer/compodoc`.\n74\t- **Risk -- `tsconfig.doc.json` path in the compodoc command**: The path `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json` must be relative to the workspace root (the `cwd` of `nx:run-commands`). Verify by running `compodoc --help` and checking that the file is found before committing.\n75\t- **Risk -- `documentation.json` location**: The `-d .` flag outputs to the workspace root. The import in `preview.ts` already points three levels up (`../../../documentation.json`) which resolves to the workspace root. These must match -- confirm before the validate step.\n76\t\n77\t## Dependencies\n78\t\n79\tSequential order required:\n80\t\n81\t- Step 1 must precede Step 2 (target must exist before `dependsOn` can reference it).\n82\t- Steps 3 and 4 are independent of steps 1/2 and of each other; they can be done in any order or in parallel.\n83\t- Step 5 (validation) must follow all other steps.\n84\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40596bc0-ad7c-4072-a632-7fd07f4bf8b4","uuid":"9f3d8864-7c25-4938-ab53-388b265ebf52","timestamp":"2026-04-24T08:18:24.230Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"D:\\projects\\github\\LayZeeDK\\ngx-smart-components\\plans\\fix-compodoc-task-graph-and-autodocs.plan.md","content":"# Plan: Fix Compodoc Task-Graph Lifecycle and Autodocs\n\n## Strategic Direction\n\n1. Add a separate `compodoc` target in `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` using `nrwl/run-commands` (or `@twittwer/compodoc:compodoc`) with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` and `-e json -d {workspaceRoot}`.\n2. Set `compodoc: false` on both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets and add `dependsOn: [\"compodoc\"]` -- this eliminates the double-run and makes the artifact contract visible to Nx.\n3. Add `tags: ['autodocs']` to the meta in `ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`; without it the compodoc JSON is dead weight.\n4. Apply Finding 2: replace the cast with a `declare global` Window augmentation in `preview.ts`.\n5. Run `npx nx reset && npx nx build-storybook ngx-smart-components` to validate cache inputs and autodocs rendering.\n\n## Steps\n\n1. **Add `compodoc` target to `project.json`**\n   - File: `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`\n   - Change: Add a new `compodoc` target using the `nx:run-commands` executor that invokes `@compodoc/compodoc` with `-p tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .` (workspace root). Set `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` so Nx can cache the artifact.\n   - Example shape:\n     ```json\n     \"compodoc\": {\n       \