{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YZeaTzS5pso3uBExqEP9az","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016U6WC7TQYyx4yByVArbJcM","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Final advisor verification for fix-compodoc-task-graph-and-autodocs plan","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:advisor","prompt":"## Review Scope\n\nImplementation of `fix-compodoc-task-graph-and-autodocs.plan.md` -- promoting Compodoc to a first-class Nx target, wiring `dependsOn`, enabling autodocs, and replacing a type cast with a typed Window augmentation in `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`.\n\n## Pre-Verified Package Behavior Claims\n\n<pre_verified source=\"packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json\" claim_id=\"pv-1\">\n  <claim>`declare global {}` is only valid in TypeScript module files (files with at least one import or export). `documentation.d.ts` has no imports or exports so `declare global` was placed in `preview.ts` instead, which has `import { global } from '@storybook/global'`.</claim>\n  <evidence method=\"Read\">TypeScript diagnostic confirmed: \"Property '__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__' does not exist on type 'Window & typeof globalThis'\" when declare global was in documentation.d.ts. Resolved by moving it to preview.ts.</evidence>\n</pre_verified>\n\n## Changes Made\n\n**Commit 1 (658345d): `packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json`**\n- Added new `compodoc` target:\n```json\n\"compodoc\": {\n  \"executor\": \"nx:run-commands\",\n  \"outputs\": [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"],\n  \"options\": {\n    \"command\": \"npx compodoc -p packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.doc.json -e json -d .\"\n  }\n}\n```\n- On both `storybook` and `build-storybook` targets: set `\"compodoc\": false`, added `\"dependsOn\": [\"compodoc\"]` at target level.\n\n**Commit 2 (658c2e4): `packages/ngx-smart-components/src/lib/ngx-smart-components/ngx-smart-components.stories.ts`**\n- Added `tags: ['autodocs']` to story meta.\n\n**Commit 3 (ec442e3): `packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/preview.ts`**\n- Added `declare global { interface Window { __STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__?: unknown; } }` directly in the file.\n- Changed assignment from `(global as Record<string, unknown>)['__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__']` to `(global as Window & typeof globalThis).__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__`.\n\n**Final state of `preview.ts`:**\n```typescript\nimport { global } from '@storybook/global';\n\ndeclare global {\n  interface Window {\n    __STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__?: unknown;\n  }\n}\n\nimport('../../../documentation.json')\n  .then(({ default: docJson }) => {\n    (global as Window & typeof globalThis).__STORYBOOK_COMPODOC_JSON__ = docJson;\n  })\n  .catch(() => undefined);\n```\n\n**`documentation.d.ts` is unchanged:**\n```typescript\ndeclare module '*/documentation.json' {\n  const value: unknown;\n  export default value;\n}\n```\n\n## Deviation from Plan\n\nPlan step 4 said to put `declare global` in `documentation.d.ts`. This produced a TypeScript error because `documentation.d.ts` has no imports/exports (script file). The fix was to place `declare global` directly in `preview.ts`, which already has an import and is therefore a module file where `declare global` is valid.\n\n## Request\n\nVerify the approach is sound and flag any concerns -- specifically: (1) is `declare global` placement in `preview.ts` correct, (2) is the `dependsOn` + `compodoc: false` pattern correct for Nx 22, (3) any issue with `outputs: [\"{workspaceRoot}/documentation.json\"]` for Nx cache tracking?"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":293,"cache_read_input_tokens":66459,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":293},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40596